2026-04-21 02:46:59 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Load module internal wiring'] hypothesis_explanation="The voltage measurements show that both lamp terminals are sitting at approximately the same potential (near 12V), so no differential voltage exists across the lamp or indicator. Tracing the connections: both 'p' terminals of the lamps inside the load module are unconnected, while both 'n' terminals are connected to the Load Input Cable (−). The protection diode's anode is wired to Load Input Cable (+), with the cathode not connected to any cable. This means that neither lamp filament is completing a circuit between + and −; the lamps are essentially floating and no current can flow through them. This points to a wiring fault internal to the load module: both 'p' terminals and the diode cathode are not properly connected to the external circuit. This would explain the persistent lack of lamp illumination, despite all voltages being correct elsewhere in the system. The internal wiring of the load module should be repaired so the correct connections (lamp 'p' to diode cathode to Load Input Cable (+) and lamp 'n' to Load Input Cable (−)) are made."
