description: Use a multimeter to check the voltage across the lamp terminals inside the load module to determine if the lamp is receiving any differential voltage. Confirm if the diode is blocking current and assess internal wiring for a possible short or misconnection., outcome='Summary of diagnostic results:\n- Both the main lamp and internal indicator lamp have 11.9765 V measured on both terminals, indicating no differential voltage across the lamps.\n- Both lamp ports labeled "p" are not connected to any cables, while both "n" ports are connected to Load Input Cable (−).\n- The Load Protection Diode anode is connected to Load Input Cable (+), while its cathode has no cable attached.\n- No polarity inversion detected in physical connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Cables between control module and load module,
description: Check the end-to-end continuity and pin mapping of each cable between the control module and the load module by testing which input terminal connects to which output terminal at both sides. Verify if there is any miswiring, swapped pairs, or short circuits between the connection points, to detect cable misconfiguration or shorted pairs., outcome='Continuity tests confirm correct mapping: Control Output Cable (+) is continuous with Load Input Cable (+), and Control Output Cable (−) with Load Input Cable (−), with no shorts or swaps between positive and negative lines. No polarity inversion detected; each positive terminal is matched to the corresponding positive, and each negative to the corresponding negative. No short circuits are present between positive and negative at either end except for your intentional bridging step.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('short_ports', 20.0), ('short_ports', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
